Previously on The Big Bang Theory

6
00:00:03,220 --> 00:00:05,450
Sheldon, did you just figure out a method

7
00:00:05,450 --> 00:00:08,350
for synthesizing a new stable super-heavy element?

8
00:00:08,350 --> 00:00:09,910
Did I?

9
00:00:10,160 --> 00:00:11,540
Well, that can't be right.

10
00:00:11,540 --> 00:00:12,960
No one's ever done that before.

11
00:00:12,960 --> 00:00:14,810
Except me, because I just did it!

12
00:00:15,250 --> 00:00:16,620
Sheldon and his brain-- yeah!

13
00:00:16,620 --> 00:00:18,650
Sheldon and his brain-- yeah!

14
00:00:19,120 --> 00:00:21,070
I've made a horrible mistake.

15
00:00:21,070 --> 00:00:22,410
What are you talking about?

16
00:00:22,410 --> 00:00:25,190
This table-- it's in square centimeters.

17
00:00:25,190 --> 00:00:26,970
I read it as square meters.

18
00:00:26,970 --> 00:00:28,440
You know what that means?

19
00:00:28,440 --> 00:00:31,420
That Americans can't handle the metric system?

20
00:00:33,300 --> 00:00:36,540
Amy, I was off by a factor of 10,000.

21
00:00:36,540 --> 00:00:38,770
But the Chinese team found the element.

22
00:00:38,770 --> 00:00:39,950
Yeah, well, they shouldn't have.

23
00:00:39,950 --> 00:00:41,730
My calculations were wrong.

24
00:00:41,730 --> 00:00:43,880
the greatest scientific achievement of my life

25
00:00:43,880 --> 00:00:45,370
is based on a blunder.

26
00:00:45,370 --> 00:00:46,900
I'm not a genius,

27
00:00:46,900 --> 00:00:48,770
I'm a fraud.

28
